38	HO TAILIEN VY KHA	cybersecvykha@gmail.com	HO TAILIEN VY KHA\nCYBER SECURITY INTERNSHIP\ncybersecvykha@gmail.com | hotallienvykha.website | 0386783066\nSUMMARY\nFinal-year Information Security student with hands-on experience in SIEM systems, log analysis, and security\nmonitoring. Strong interest in cybersecurity risk assessment, security controls, and compliance frameworks\nsuch as 1SO 27001 and NIST. Experienced in building Al-assisted workflows for log analysis, incident\ninterpretation, and security monitoring to enhance threat detection and response efficiency. Seeking a\nCybersecurity Risk Advisory Internship and SOC internship to support organizations in identifying risks,\nimproving security posture, incident response, threat detection and implementing effective security controls.\nEDUCATION\nFPT University\nNov 2022 - Present\n« Information Assurance - GPA 3.0/4.0\nPROJECTS\nAutomated Hybrid Malware Analysis System - Study Project\n« Builta hybrid analysis pipeline combining CAPEV2 Sandbox (dynamic analysis) and Machine Learning\nmodels to enhance cyber threat detection capabiities.\n+ Automated system deployment and dependency management using Docker and Shell scripting, ensuring a\nconsistent and isolated analysis environment.\nTech stack: Python, CAPEv2, Docker, VirtualBox, Linux (Ubuntu).\nCyber Range Platform - Capstone Project\n+ Deployed virtualized environment using Proxmox VE; implemented centralized logging and active\ndefense systems integrating Wazuh SIEM and Nginx WAF (ModSecurity) to monitor, analyze, and block\nmalicious traffic.\nDeveloped an Al Analyzer Service (SOC Copilot) utiizing Retrieval-Augmented Genaration (RAG).\nLeveraged Qdrant vector database to retrieve highly accurate attack contexts (e.g., SQLI, XSS), improving\nsystem reliability and reducing incorrect LLM responses.\nDesigned automated and live-fire Red vs. Blue scenarios where Al assistants (Cyber Shell & SOC Copilot)\nanalyze attack commands, summarize real-time incident reports, and recommend mitigation rules to\nfacilitate automated security training.\n+ Tech stack: Python, Wazuh, Docker, Nginx, ModSecurity, FastAPI, LangGraph, Qdrant, Linux\nWORK EXPERIENCE\nGENERAL ERA DIGITAL SOLUTION JOINT STOCK COMPANY\nJanuary 10, 2024 - April 10, 2024\n« Security Infrastructure: Participated in deploying and configuring security services and internal\ninfrastructure to enhance the company's defense posture.\n« Cloud Security: Implemented and managed cloud protection measures using Cloudfiare (WAF, DNS,\nand DDoS mitigation) to safeguard web applications.\n« System Hardening: Assisted in optimizing server security and ensuring compliance with basic\nsecurity standards.\nSKILLS\nCybersecurity & Risk\n+ Log analysis, event monitoring, alert triage\n+ SIEM: Wazuh, ELK Stack\n+ Basic risk identification and security assessment\n+ Understanding of security controls and mitigation strategies\nSystems\n& Networking\n« Linux (Ubunty, Kali), Windows Server\n+ TCP/IP, CCNA fundamentals\nProgramming\n& Tools\n« Python, Bash (basic scripting & automation)\n» Tools: Elastic, Burp Suite, Cloudflare\nFrameworks & Knowledge\n« ISO/IEC 27001 & 27002 (basic understanding)\n« NIST Cybersecurity Framework (Identify, Protect, Detect, Respond)\n+ OWASP Top 10 (Web Application Security Risks)\n» MITRE ATT&CK Framework (basic mapping of threats and techniques)\nACHIEVEMENTS AND CERTIFICATE\n« Connect and Protect: Networks and Network Security - Google Certificate\n« Top 4 - FIA CTF CYBERSUS 2025\n« Certified Cybersecurity Educator Professional (CCEP) - Red Team Leader\n« Certified Red Team Operations Management (CRTOM) - Red Team Leader\n« Ethical Hacker - Cisco Academy\n» CCNA: Switching, Routing, and Wireless Essentials - Cisco Academy\nADDITIONAL INFORMATION\n« English: Intermediate\n+ Willing to work shifts\n+ Strong self-learning mindset and adaptability	Python\nBash\nCAPEv2\nMachine Learning\nFastAPI\nLangGraph\nQdrant\nWazuh\nELK Stack\nNginx\nModSecurity\nVirtualBox\nProxmox VE\nLinux\nCloudflare\nDocker\nSIEM\nCybersecurity risk assessment\nSecurity monitoring\nLog analysis\nThreat detection\nIncident response\nSecurity controls\nCompliance frameworks\nSecurity infrastructure\nCloud security\nSystem hardening\nVirtualized environments\nCentralized logging\nActive defense\nWeb application security\nRAG\nMITRE ATT&CK\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework\nISO/IEC 27001\nISO/IEC 27002\nOWASP Top 10\nTCP/IP\nCCNA fundamentals\nAlert triage\nEvent monitoring\nSecurity assessment\nMitigation strategies\nThreat mapping	new	2026-05-14 08:45:10.806144+00	2026-05-14 08:47:43.606123+00	cv_pdf	Cyber Security InternShip.pdf	processed	llm_hybrid	0.95	synced	\N	2026-05-14 08:45:47.698492+00	{"summary": "Final-year Information Security student with hands-on experience in SIEM systems, log analysis, and security monitoring. Strong interest in cybersecurity risk assessment, security controls, and compliance frameworks such as ISO 27001 and NIST. Experienced in building AI-assisted workflows for log analysis, incident interpretation, and security monitoring to enhance threat detection and response efficiency. Seeking a Cybersecurity Risk Advisory Internship and SOC internship to support organizations in identifying risks, improving security posture, incident response, threat detection, and implementing effective security controls.", "technical_skills": [{"name": "Python", "canonical": "python", "source": "llm_structured", "section_origin": "education", "aliases": ["python"], "confidence": 0.99, "skill_groups": ["backend", "data", "ai_ml"], "prerequisites": [], "related_skills": ["fastapi", "airflow", "dbt"], "specializations": ["programming_language"], "classification_target": "technical_skills", "evidence": [{"text": "Tech stack: Python, CAPEv2, Docker, VirtualBox, Linux (Ubuntu).", "section_origin": "education", "confidence": 0.99}, {"text": "Tech stack: Python, Wazuh, Docker, Nginx, ModSecurity, FastAPI, LangGraph, Qdrant, Linux", "secti