18	Software Developer	Contract remote Software Developer role focused on designing, developing, and delivering robust back-end and full-stack solutions using modern programming languages and full-stack technologies in a collaborative, distributed environment.	Python\nRust\nGoLang\nJava\nNode.js\nAndroid\niOS\nJavaScript\nAWS\nGCP\nAzure\nCloud platforms\nVersion Control\nCI/CD\nDevOps principles\nContainerization\nModern Development Tools\nSoftware Development\nBack-end Development\nFull-stack Development\nScalable Software Systems\nReliable and maintainable software systems\nSoftware engineering best practices\nClean, efficient, and well-documented code\nTroubleshooting and debugging\nCode optimization\nCode reviews\nTechnical discussions\nArchitectural planning\nSoftware development lifecycle\nTesting and deployment\nAgile Environments	draft	2026-05-12 16:24:05.279337+00	2026-05-12 16:24:05.282675+00	Design, implement, and maintain scalable back-end and full-stack applications using Python, Rust, GoLang, Java, or Node.js.\nCollaborate closely with cross-functional team members to deliver high-quality software solutions that meet evolving business requirements.\nWrite clean, efficient, and well-documented code, following best software engineering practices.\nTroubleshoot, debug, and optimize existing codebases to improve performance and reliability.\nParticipate in code reviews, technical discussions, and architectural planning to drive continuous improvement.\nContribute to the full software development lifecycle, from concept and design to testing and deployment.\nMaintain clear, concise, and thoughtful written and verbal communication across distributed teams.	3+ years of hands-on experience in software development with one or more of the following: Python, Rust, GoLang, Java, Node.js, Android, IOS or full-stack development.\nProficiency in building scalable, reliable, and maintainable software systems.\nExperience working in remote, collaborative, and agile environments.\nExpertise in modern development tools, version control systems, and CI/CD pipelines.\nStrong problem-solving skills with keen attention to detail.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills, with a high standard for clarity and professionalism.\nSelf-driven, proactive, and able to work independently in a distributed setting.\nExperience with cloud platforms such as AWS, GCP, or Azure.\nKnowledge of DevOps principles and containerization technologies.	About the job\nJob Title: Software Developer\n\nJob Type: Contract\n\nLocation: Remote\n\nJob Summary\n\nJoin our customers team as a Software Developer, where innovation, ownership, and technical\nexpertise drive every project. You’ll collaborate with a dynamic and diverse team to design,\ndevelop, and deliver robust solutions using modern programming languages and full-stack\ntechnologies. If you are passionate about building scalable applications and thrive in a remote\nand communicative environment, we want to hear from you.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n•\nDesign, implement, and maintain scalable back-end and full-stack applications using\nPython, Rust, GoLang, Java, or Node.js.\n•\nCollaborate closely with cross-functional team members to deliver high-quality software\nsolutions that meet evolving business requirements.\n•\nWrite clean, efficient, and well-documented code, following best software engineering\npractices.\n•\nTroubleshoot, debug, and optimize existing codebases to improve performance and\nreliability.\n•\nParticipate in code reviews, technical discussions, and architectural planning to drive\ncontinuous improvement.\n•\nContribute to the full software development lifecycle, from concept and design to testing\nand deployment.\n•\nMaintain clear, concise, and thoughtful written and verbal communication across\ndistributed teams.\n\nRequired Skills And Qualifications\n\n•\n3+ years of hands-on experience in software development with one or more of the\nfollowing: Python, Rust, GoLang, Java, Node.js, Android, IOS or full-stack development\n(backend or full-stack).\n•\nProficiency in building scalable, reliable, and maintainable software systems.\n•\nExperience working in remote, collaborative, and agile environments.\n•\nExpertise in modern development tools, version control systems, and CI/CD pipelines.\n•\nStrong problem-solving skills with keen attention to detail.\n•\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills, with a high standard for clarity and\nprofessionalism.\n•\nSelf-driven, proactive, and able to work independently in a distributed setting.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n•\nExperience with cloud platforms such as AWS, GCP, or Azure.\n•\nKnowledge of DevOps principles and containerization technologies.	jd_pdf	SEYO.pdf	processed	{"title": "Software Developer", "summary": "Contract remote Software Developer role focused on designing, developing, and delivering robust back-end and full-stack solutions using modern programming languages and full-stack technologies in a collaborative, distributed environment.", "required_skills": [{"name": "Python", "canonical": "python", "source": "llm_structured", "section_origin": "qualifications", "aliases": ["python"], "confidence": 0.98, "importance": 5, "requirement_type": "must_have", "skill_groups": ["ai_ml", "backend", "data"], "prerequisites": [], "related_skills": ["airflow", "dbt", "fastapi"], "specializations": ["programming_language"], "classification_target": "technical_skills"}, {"name": "Rust", "canonical": "rust", "source": "llm_structured", "section_origin": "qualifications", "aliases": ["rust"], "confidence": 0.98, "importance": 5, "requirement_type": "must_have", "skill_groups": ["backend"], "prerequisites": [], "related_skills": ["docker"], "specializations": ["programming_language"], "classification_target": "technical_skills"}, {"name": "GoLang", "canonical": "golang", "source": "llm_structured", "section_origin": "qualifications", "aliases": ["golang", "go"], "confidence": 0.